- Iterators (using Biotech's xenotypes, small chance to appear in transport pod crashes, must be supplied with neuron flies OR connected to a can) Iterators are incredibly intelligent, have a higher natural learning speed, but are very fragile and wimpy, most pain is enough to knock them out.
- Neuron flies spawn very rarely (like 0.0001%) in all biomes. They must either be downed or tamed in order to perform an operation to render them usable. Killing them destroys their potential. Once converted into a stable neuron, it can be used via gizmo on iterators to remove their disabled hediff and bring them back. They are very weak and have almost no HP, making it difficult to obtain one safely outside of taming. Outside of iterators, they can be used by normal pawns as a skilltrainer of a random variety.
- Cans are late-game structures (10x10) that require a lot of advanced resources to create, including a persona core (?). Very power hungry and generates a lot of heat, increases chances of rain and thunderstorms. Cans can be psycically connected to an Iterator, curing them of the disabled hediff. Downside to Cans unlike nueron flies is that if a Can is destroyed it will sever all connections to its Iterator and disable them again. When a can is temporarily disabled, it will also temporarily disable its iterator.
- Blue lizards
- Monks plant a karma flower on death (1% chance)
- Overseers (rare spawns that happen anywhere, can dodge projectiles and attacks 99% chance, capable of teleporting. Drops Overseer Eye, can be sold for the same value as a pearl and can be implanted into pawns, providing them increased research speed and dodge chances. If tamed, they can be trained to use an ability to increase research speed on all colony pawns)
- add rjw support
- Animal gear support


batnip to grenade chain
- grow batnip plants to produce harvested batnip (batnip plants should make batflies spawn on the map)
- harvested batnip can be used directly as food, rolled into a non-addictive blunt for a small high, or combined with chemfuel to create harvested cherrybomb
- cherrybomb plants can be grown traditionally, but at the cost of requiring a level 16+ farmer
- harvested cherrybombs cannot be eaten, but they can be combined with leather to create a grenade-belt cherrybomb pouch that is fueled by harvested cherrybombs that damages (weakly) and stuns pawns in the radius OR combined with pearls to create scavenger grenades
- scavenger grenades cannot be used by themselves, but a belt must be created to store them. these grenades have a smaller radius and do more damage than vanilla grenades